article.headline: Wright St 58, Cleveland St. 55
article.story: CLEVELAND (AP) -- DaShaun Wood had 12 points and 10 rebounds in Wright State's 58-55 win over Cleveland State on Thursday night. Drew Burleson had 11 points and Jordon Pleiman added 10 points and six rebounds for the Raiders (5-6, 2-0 Horizon League). Wright State was up 30-29 at halftime. The Raiders opened the second half with a 11-0 run and led for the rest of the game. The Vikings (4-8, 0-3) answered with six straight points and cut the deficit to two points on a 3-pointer from Raheem Moss with 41 seconds left, but couldn't pull ahead. Moss led the Vikings with 18 points and Frashon McGee added 14 points and seven rebounds. Wright State had 38 rebounds to 25 for the Vikings. Cleveland State scored 24 points off 20 Raiders turnovers, but committed 13 turnovers of their own.
